                  "D-D"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Through the 2H(d,n) reaction in the deuterium",
                "gas target, quasi-monoenergetic neutrons were",
                "produced. During the measurement, the deuteron beam",
                "current was about 1.2 uA, and the neutron energy was",
                "5.0 MeV in the direction of 0 degree with respect to",
                "the deuteron beam line."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A 232Th(OH) 4 sample was located at the cathodes of",
                "the TPC with diameter of 44.0 mm, thickness of 601.9",
                "ug/cm2, number of nuclei of 1.808E19."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TPC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The time projection chamber was used as the",
                "fission fragments detector."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FISCH",
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The small parallel plate fission chamber",
                "was used for the determination of the absolute",
                "neutron flux. The EJ309 scintillator detector was",
                "used as neutron detector to determine neutron energy",
                "spectrum with the unfolding method."
              ]
            }
          ],
